---
const flowSteps = [
  'Refinement',
  'Milestone',
  'Phases',
  'PRDs',
  'Implementation',
  'Report',
  'Loop',
]
---

<section aria-label="Why DIP" class="border-b border-zinc-800/50">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-32">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white tracking-tight">
      Why DIP?
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-base sm:text-lg text-zinc-400 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed">
      AI coding agents are powerful, but they struggle without structure. Throwing an entire epic
      at an agent produces inconsistent results. DIP solves this by breaking complex work into
      well-scoped, document-driven units that agents can execute reliably.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-10 sm:mt-16 grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8">
      <article class="rounded-xl border border-red-500/10 bg-red-500/[0.02] p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-white flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-red-500/10 text-red-400 text-sm font-bold flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">!</span>
          The Problem
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm sm:text-base text-zinc-400">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/40 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            Agents lack context about the bigger picture
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/40 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            Large features get implemented inconsistently
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/40 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            No structured handoff between planning and execution
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-1.5 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/40 flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            Phase transitions lose context without documentation
          </li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/10 bg-cyan-500/[0.02] p-5 sm:p-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold text-white flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-cyan-500/10 text-cyan-400 text-sm font-bold flex-shrink-0" aria-hidden="true">&#10003;</span>
          The Solution
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-sm sm:text-base text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
          DIP provides a repeatable loop where each step produces a document that feeds into the next,
          creating a chain of context that keeps both humans and agents aligned.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-5 rounded-lg border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-950/80 p-4">
          <div class="hidden sm:block">
            <code class="text-sm text-cyan-400 font-mono leading-relaxed">
              Refinement → Milestone → Phases → PRDs → Implementation → Report → Loop
            </code>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5 sm:hidden">
            {flowSteps.map((step, i) => (
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span class="w-5 h-5 rounded flex items-center justify-center bg-cyan-400/10 text-cyan-400 text-[10px] font-mono font-bold flex-shrink-0">
                  {i + 1}
                </span>
                <span class="text-sm text-cyan-400 font-mono">{step}</span>
                {i < flowSteps.length - 1 && (
                  <span class="text-zinc-700 text-xs ml-auto" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
                )}
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
